    wiki:"Seven_Years%27_War",
    overview:"The Seven Years War (1756–1763) was the first war fought across multiple continents simultaneously — Europe, North America, India, the Caribbean, West Africa, and the Philippines. Britain and Prussia faced France, Austria, Russia, Sweden, and Spain. British naval supremacy (Admiral Hawke's victory at Quiberon Bay) allowed the Royal Navy to seize French colonies everywhere. The Treaty of Paris (1763) transferred Canada and the Ohio Valley to Britain, Spanish Florida, and most French Caribbean islands. Britain emerged as the world's dominant colonial power — the foundation of the British Empire at its zenith.",
