    overview:"The Songhai Empire succeeded the Mali Empire as the dominant power in West Africa, reaching its peak under Sunni Ali (r. 1464–1492) and Askia the Great (r. 1493–1528). At its peak it stretched from the Atlantic coast to modern-day Niger. Timbuktu, the empire's intellectual capital, had three universities (the Sankore being the most famous) and 25,000 students, with a library of 700,000 manuscripts. The empire was destroyed by a Moroccan invasion (Battle of Tondibi, 1591) using firearms — the first defeat of a major West African power by gunpowder weapons.",
