    wiki:"ARPANET",
    overview:"The Advanced Research Projects Agency Network (ARPANET), funded by the US Defense Department, sent its first message on October 29, 1969: Charley Kline at UCLA tried to type 'LOGIN' to Stanford; the system crashed after 'LO.' The network grew to connect research universities. TCP/IP protocol (1983) established the internet's technical foundation. Tim Berners-Lee's World Wide Web (1991) added a user-friendly layer. Commercial use opened in 1995. The internet grew from 16 million users (1995) to 5 billion (2023).",
    impact:["5 billion internet users today — humanity's dominant information infrastructure","E-commerce ($5.8 trillion/year), social media, streaming, and remote work all require the internet","The internet democratized information — Wikipedia, Khan Academy, Project Gutenberg — making knowledge universally free","Also democratized disinformation — the internet's greatest unresolved challenge"]
