    wiki:"Panama_Canal",
    overview:"The US took over France's abandoned canal project and built the Panama Canal (1904–1914) at a cost of $375 million (about $11 billion today) and 25,000–27,500 workers' lives — mostly from yellow fever and malaria. The canal uses a system of locks to raise ships 85 feet over the Continental Divide. It opened August 15, 1914 (weeks after WWI began). The first transit: SS Ancon. The canal shortened the New York–San Francisco voyage from 13,000 miles (around Cape Horn) to 5,200 miles. The US controlled the Canal Zone until 1999.",
