    wiki:"M%C4%81ori_people",
    overview:"New Zealand was one of the last major landmasses settled by humans. Eastern Polynesian navigators (from the Cook Islands / Society Islands area) arrived in New Zealand (Aotearoa — 'Land of the Long White Cloud') around 1280–1320 CE in a series of voyages. They found a temperate land rich in birds (including the giant moa and Haast's eagle) and marine life. Their descendants, the Maori, developed a sophisticated Polynesian culture with distinctive art (ta moko tattoos, whakairo carving), oral traditions, and organized tribal warfare. The Maori remained the sole inhabitants until Abel Tasman's 1642 European contact.",
