    wiki:"SpaceX",
    overview:"Founded by Elon Musk in 2002 with $100 million of his own money, SpaceX survived near-bankruptcy (three failed Falcon 1 launches) to revolutionize the rocket industry. Falcon 9's first landing on a drone ship (December 2015) proved reusability; costs fell from $54,000/kg to $2,500/kg to orbit. SpaceX launched NASA astronauts in 2020 (ending US dependence on Russian Soyuz), deployed 5,000+ Starlink satellites (creating a global internet constellation), and is developing Starship (the largest rocket in history) for Mars missions. By 2023 SpaceX conducted more orbital launches than any nation.",
