    wiki:"Google",
    overview:"Larry Page and Sergey Brin launched Google.com in September 1998, funded by a $100,000 check from Andy Bechtolsheim. PageRank — ranking web pages by the quality of links to them — produced dramatically better search results than competitors. Google's advertising model (paying only for clicks) and AdWords (2000) created a $200 billion/year advertising business. Gmail (2004), Google Maps (2005), Android (2008), and YouTube (acquisition, 2006) extended Google's reach. By 2020, Google processed 8.5 billion searches per day — answering more questions per minute than were asked in all of human history before 1998.",
    impact:["8.5 billion searches/day — Google became humanity's primary information access tool","PageRank changed how content was created — SEO became a major industry","Google Maps revolutionized navigation — GPS devices, paper maps, and most travel agencies ceased to be economically viable","Android operating system runs 72% of the world's smartphones — Google's second existential platform","'Don't be evil' original motto — controversially dropped in 2018"]
