    wiki:"Chinese_Civil_War",
    overview:"The Chinese Civil War had its roots in the 1927 Shanghai Massacre when Chiang Kai-shek turned on his Communist allies. Two decades of alternating conflict, cooperation against Japan (1937–1945), and resumed warfare followed. After WWII the Communists controlled north China with a battle-hardened army and broad rural support. The Nationalist army's corruption and hyperinflation discredited the government. By 1949, Nationalist forces collapsed; Chiang and 1.5 million Nationalists fled to Taiwan. Mao proclaimed the People's Republic on October 1, 1949.",
