    wiki:"Bengal_famine_of_1943",
    overview:"In 1943, a combination of cyclone, rice disease, and wartime disruption reduced Bengal's food supply. The British colonial government and Winston Churchill's War Cabinet prioritized food exports and military supply while the famine was worsening. Internal British documents show Churchill blocked emergency grain shipments to India, reportedly saying Bengal could wait or suggesting 'Why hasn't Gandhi died yet?' 2–3 million Bengalis died. The famine deepened Indian resentment of British rule and contributed to the independence movement.",
