    wiki:"Division_of_Korea",
    overview:"As Japan surrendered in August 1945, the US and Soviet Union hastily divided Korea at the 38th Parallel to accept Japanese surrenders — with no Korean input. The line was drawn in 30 minutes by US Army officers Dean Rusk and Charles Bonesteel on an National Geographic map. Two separate states emerged: the US-backed Republic of Korea in the south and the Soviet-backed People's Republic in the north under Kim Il-sung. Both claimed to be Korea's legitimate government. The Korean War (1950–1953) hardened the division. The 38th Parallel remains the world's most fortified border.",
